\begin_layout Section
Nuclear structure and estimate of nuclear radii
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Shell Model
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Levels of shell within the nucleus, creating the potential well with quantized
 levels.
 Max nucleon in each level.
 Pauli exclusion principal are filled according to the Pauli Exclusion Principle.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Magic Numbers!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Liquid Drop Model
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Number of forces hold the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

droplet
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 together.
 Binding between atoms occurs between every nucleon with surface tension
 correction.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
M=NM_{n}+ZM_{p}-\alpha A+\beta A^{2/3}+\gamma\frac{Z^{2}}{A^{1/3}}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

